Hanart TZ Gallery is delighted to announce 17 pieces of work from Sim Chi Yin’s “One Day We’ll Understand” project are now in the of collection of M+ Museum.

Started in 2015, “One Day We’ll Understand” is an ongoing project, looking at the history and memory of the 12-year conflict between the British colonial government and the resistance led by the Malayan leftists (from 1948 to 1960). 

